<headline>Special Weather Statement issued August 24 at 3:17PM EDT  by NWS Blacksburg</headline>
<description>...A STRONG THUNDERSTORM WILL IMPACT SOUTHEASTERN STOKES AND WESTERN
ROCKINGHAM COUNTIES THROUGH 345 PM EDT...
At 316 PM EDT, Doppler radar was tracking a strong thunderstorm over
Madison, moving southeast at 30 mph.
HAZARD...Wind gusts up to 40 mph and pea size hail.
SOURCE...Radar indicated.
IMPACT...Gusty winds could knock down tree limbs and blow around
unsecured objects. Minor hail damage to vegetation is
possible.
Locations impacted include...
Wentworth...
Mayodan...
Madison...
Stoneville...
Pine Hall...
Intelligence...
and Ellisboro.
MAX HAIL SIZE...0.25 IN
MAX WIND GUST...40 MPH</description>
<instruction>If outdoors, consider seeking shelter inside a building.</instruction>
